message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. The paper deals with automatic question generation from text, which is a task related to natural language processing and machine learning. The paper proposes a novel generator-evaluator framework that optimizes objectives related to semantics and structure, which are important aspects of NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are all related to NLP and machine learning. The sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible, as they deal with neural networks and text processing, respectively.
